INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (21, 1, '2009-12-01 10:35:54', '2009-12-01 10:35:54', '<div>The most amazing cake frosting is also the easiest.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>RECIPE:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>255g dark chocolate (at least 53% cocoa liqueur)</li>\r\n	<li>1 cup cream</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>There are two methods for making ganache - I prefer the second one, even if it does take a bit more effort!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>Method 1: </strong>Melt the chocolate in a double boiler; add the chilled cream and stir until smooth. Don\'t give up! The mixture will take a minute or two to come together into a smooth pourable/spreadable frosting. Use it almost straight away, as it will set pretty quickly.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><strong>Method 2: </strong>Chop chop chop the chocolate as finely as you can - or shave it using a grater. Place in a mixing bowl. Bring the cream to a boil and pour over the chocolate then stir until smooth. You\'re done!</div>', 'Basic ganache recipe', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-2', '', '', '2009-12-01 10:35:54', '2009-12-01 10:35:54', '', 13, 'http://localhost:8000/bakerofbrighton/2009/12/01/13-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2, 1, '2009-11-14 11:41:28', '2009-11-14 11:41:28', '<img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-75" title="me" src="/images/2009/11/me-267x167.jpg" alt="" width="267" height="167" />\r\n\r\nHi, I\'m Alex, a designer by day and baker by every other spare minute. I live in beautiful Brighton, home to some <a href="http://localhost:8000/bakerofbrighton/brighton-baking-guide/">great chocolate makers and patisseries</a>.\r\n\r\nMy fondness for baking escalated about 2 years ago, when I realised what a fantastic creative outlet it could be. Losing myself in something tangible and non-computery was a wonderful release and I\'ve since made everything from breads to delicate genoise to cupcakes and macaroons. Not to mention that I\'ve found kneading dough is great for RSI :-)\r\n<h3>Contacting me about baking for you</h3>\r\nI love baking for parties, special occasions and charity events. If you\'d like my help in creating that perfect , just use the contact form below. ', 'About your host', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'contact', '', '', '2013-01-06 14:07:46', '2013-01-06 14:07:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/bakerofbrighton/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 3) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (543, 1, '2013-05-05 22:18:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'I\'ve not blogged since I started my master\'s degree a year and a half ago. \n\nMuch has happened since, at least by my modest standards. I\'ve changed jobs three times. I\'ve crammed my life full of new people, adventures, projects. It\'s been good - but I only want more. It\'s all left little time for baking. \n\nIt\'s hard to know when you\'re trying hard enough, especially when you\'re as rootless as I have been and as shy and as doubtful of my own abilities as I have always been.\n\nWhat I do know is that for most of 2012 I had a pretty shitty time of it. While I ran about trying new things, making new friends and doing projects, my mind folded in on itself and, sometime around my birthday in October, collapsed into a heap. I didn\'t tell anyone\n\nI can\'t blame anyone but myself, but I have to say this: I have finally finally finally, after years of not really. ', 'Tired and grateful: the cake', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-05-05 22:18:56', '2013-05-05 22:18:56', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8000/bakerofbrighton/?p=543', 0, 'post', '', 0) ; 
