. Allow to cool to room temperature then cover the surface with cling f\n\nFor the pastry:\n1. Whirl the icing sugar and flour together in a food processor. Sprinkle on the butter and give it a few more spins till the mixture resembles fine sand. Mix the egg yolk with a bit of ice water and add to bind the pastry. Add just enough water to bind then dumb the dough onto \n2. Bake the tartlets at 170 degrees for about 12-15 mins until just golden. Leave to cool, then fill with pastry cream and decorate with fresh strawberries and a sliver of basil leaf. \n\n', 'Strawberry tarts with basil-infused pastry cream', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '236-revision-5', '', '', '2010-06-15 17:17:31', '2010-06-15 17:17:31', '', 236, 'http://localhost:8000/bakerofbrighton/236-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
