INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (528, 1, '2011-09-06 09:36:16', '2011-09-06 09:36:16', '&nbsp;\n\nHas it really been  more than a month? The last recipe I posted here, with its cucumber and elderflower flavours, defined the height of summer. This one feels like summer\'s crescendo. There is something about plums and apricots, the way their flavours change, intensify and darken during baking that defines early autumn for me. And autumn has certainly arrived with fierce conviction,  first with mists and then with lashing winds and rain as soon as September began.\n\nPlums and apricots do pair so beautifully with frangipane, sinking into its almondy depths like into a warm duvet.\n\nRECIPE:\n\nFor the pastry:\n<ul>\n	<li>200g plain flour</li>\n	<li>80g icing sugar</li>\n	<li>butter</li>\n	<li>egg yolk</li>\n	<li>ice water to bind</li>\n</ul>\nFor the frangipane and fruit:\n<ul>\n	<li>2 eggs</li>\n	<li>170g  icing sugar</li>\n	<li>170g  ground almonds</li>\n	<li>170g unsalted butter</li>\n	<li>A few drops almond essence</li>\n</ul>\n1 lbs apricots, sliced into 8 even pieces\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Apricot frangipane tartlets', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '527-revision', '', '', '2011-09-06 09:36:16', '2011-09-06 09:36:16', '', 527, 'http://localhost:8000/bakerofbrighton/527-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
